  "text": "The computational details closely follow what has been done in the quenched case discussed in refs. [CITATION_1] 15] . To suppress excited B-meson state contributions to the correlation functions, we introduce wave functions ω(x) at the boundaries of the SF such that the correlators f stat A and f stat 1 (cf. eqs. (2.10) -(2.12) in section 2) take the form",
